8. c5
9. c4 {Again: when Black plays ...c5 it costs a tempo (pawn moves are not developing moves) and because the value of time goes up when the position opens our time advantage is now worth more.} 
9. Qxb2
10. Rd1 {A beautiful move, we recognize that Black's queen needs to take on d4 and our rook dreams of Rd8 with a Morphy mate.} 
10. Qxd4
11. Qb3
11. Qxe5+
12. Ne2
12. Qc7
13. cxd5
13. exd5
14. O-O {Black will get mated.} 
