[Result "*"]

1. e4
1. d6
2. d4
2. Nf6
3. Nc3
3. g6
4. Be3 {Strategy. O-O-O, Qd2-Bh6, h4-h5, wiggle the lady into h6 and then mate Black's king. Making it easy. We have a simple attacking formation whose dynamics can be understood at a glance.Style. Let's contrast this with the Austrian Attack (4.f4). That's a plan that plays for space, we play for mate.} 
4. Ng4 {The problem with this move is that the knight won't be able to stay here, so we'll likely see a retreat with loss of tempo.} 
5. Bg5
5. h6
6. Bh4
6. Bg7
7. Qd2
7. O-O
8. O-O-O
8. c6
9. f4 {We are now going to roll Black up.} 
9. b5
10. e5 {The g4-knight is gone, h3 on its way.} 
