5. Qd2
5. O-O
6. O-O-O
6. c6
7. Bh6 {A great rule of thumb in fianchetto positions: only spend a tempo on Bh6 if you are playing for mate. We are playing for mate.} 
7. b5
8. f3
8. Qa5
9. h4 {The plan seen here shows the general mechanics of our mating attack: Bh6, h4-h5, bring the lady to h6.} 
9. b4
10. Nb1
10. Qxa2 {Black may feel like they've accomplished something, but the queen is a long way from her man and we have the jump.} 
11. h5
11. Nbd7
12. hxg6
12. fxg6 {Only move.} 
13. Bxg7
13. Kxg7
14. Qh6+ {The lady has arrived.} 
14. Kf7
15. Nh3
15. Ke8
16. Ng5 {Black is going to get mated.} 
