5. c6 {This is the move Scandi players love.} 
6. Bd2 {SPARRING POSITIONSimple chess, the queen on a5 will owe us more time. 'Don't develop your queen early.'} 
6. Bf5
7. Bc4 {The threat of Nd5 jumpstarts our attack.} 
7. Nbd7
8. Qe2
8. Bxc2
9. Nb5
9. Qd8
10. Nd6 {Checkmate.} 
