20. Nxe5
21. Rxe5 {Here a remarkable thing happened: White was upset at the way the opening went. The position felt like a mess, and it didn't look like anything seen in the prep.But if we take a moment we'll immediately see that Black is in big trouble because it's impossible for him to connect the rooks. Remember: castling privileges have been lost!} 
21. Kf8 {Doesn't look right, but it's hard to give advice.} 
22. Qe2 {22.Bd2!White's claim: we are winning because we are up a rook. Not playing Bd2 is similar to not playing Nc3: White was focused on variations instead of fixing their worst pieces.} 
