13. Ngf6 {At this point, White still had one hour and 33 minutes left!Let us take special note of this chess crime and put it in the context of our project: This game is typical of how repertoire games typically go, several decisive positions have occurred before we've reached move 15. But White has treated it as a blitz game, moving quickly in a macho kind of way to impress with the power of the repertoire.By reviewing games like this, we learn that we have to be prepared to tank early. It's an entirely different kind of chess from say a London where White can play intuitive moves for a while.And the reason is that we are the ones who have raised the temperature of the water to a raging boil - and we are also the ones who might get burned!} 
